The paper deals with fine-grained recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The approach proposed in the paper involves training a model using free, noisy data from the web, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the scalability of the approach, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
